The paper deals with distributed computing on large-scale graphs, which is a topic that falls under the categories of Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also uses information-theoretic techniques to establish lower bounds, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper presents algorithms for two fundamental graph problems, PageRank and Triangle Enumeration, which are topics that fall under the categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
